---
import DocLayout from '../../../layouts/DocLayout.astro';
const lang = 'en';
const phases = [
  {
    ver: 'v0.1', name: 'Alpha MVP', period: 'Months 1–3', status: 'current',
    items: [
      'Installable PWA with offline observation queue',
      'Photo ID: Claude Haiku 4.5 + PlantNet cascade',
      'Spanish UI + Zapoteco pilot (FPIC process with Sierra Norte community)',
      'Darwin Core data model with NOM-059 taxon subset',
      'CSV / Darwin Core Archive export',
      'Target: 50–200 beta users in Oaxaca',
    ],
    not: ['Video', 'Audio AI', 'Camera traps', 'Gamification', 'Scout chat', 'Institutional export'],
  },
  {
    ver: 'v0.5', name: 'Beta', period: 'Months 4–6', status: 'planned',
    items: [
      'BirdNET audio ID (commercial license from Cornell)',
      'Multi-image observations',
      'Ecological evidence: structured fields (substrate, stride, track morphology, scat)',
      'Rastrum Scout v0 — conversational ID disambiguator',
      'Research-grade consensus: iNat-style 2/3 identifier agreement',
      'Local Contexts BC Notice integration',
      'GBIF IPT pilot publish',
      'Target: 500–2,000 users across 2 states',
    ],
  },
  {
    ver: 'v1.0', name: 'Public Launch', period: 'Months 7–12', status: 'planned',
    items: [
      'Camera trap ingestion (SpeciesNet + MegaDetector compatible)',
      'Video support: ≤30s clips, auto-transcoded H.265/AV1',
      'Opt-in gamification (no leaderboards, no FOMO)',
      'Institutional exports: MIA, UMA, SNIB, INAH formats',
      'Credentialed-researcher access tier for sensitive species coordinates',
      'EXIF/metadata auto-extraction',
      'Lunar/weather environmental enrichment',
      'Target: 5+ states, 10K+ users',
    ],
  },
  {
    ver: 'v1.5', name: 'Territory Layer', period: 'Months 10–14', status: 'planned',
    items: [
      'Biodiversity Trails with GPS waypoints + diversity metrics',
      'PITs (Puntos de Información Territorial) + QR code generation',
      'GeoJSON map layers: ANP/INEGI/INAH/hydrological boundaries',
      'Diversity indices: S, H\', D (Simpson), Chao1, Pielou J, rarefaction curves',
      'Phenological calendar per site',
      'Darwin Core + R community matrix export',
    ],
  },
  {
    ver: 'v2.0', name: 'Institutional', period: 'Months 15–20', status: 'planned',
    items: [
      'Camera trap advanced: occupancy modeling, activity histograms, multi-camera grids',
      'Formal GBIF dataset publisher + DOI generation',
      'CONABIO SNIB, CONANP ANP, INAH biocultural formats',
      'Regional ML model training pipeline (Oaxaca-endemic focus)',
      'B2G SaaS dashboard for CONANP / state agencies',
    ],
  },
  {
    ver: 'v2.5', name: 'AI + AR', period: 'Months 21–30', status: 'planned',
    items: [
      'Rastrum Scout — full conversational field AI with regional RAG',
      'AR species overlay in camera viewfinder',
      'pgvector semantic species search',
      'CONABIO/CONANP/INAH formal partnership APIs',
      'Indigenous language voice I/O (Zapoteco, Mixteco, Náhuatl, Maya)',
    ],
  },
];
---
<DocLayout title="Roadmap" lang={lang} section="roadmap">

# 🗺️ Roadmap

Rastrum ships in six milestones over 30 months. The MVP is intentionally narrow — prove offline works, then expand.

<div class="not-prose space-y-0 mt-8">
  {phases.map((p, i) => (
    <div class="relative pl-10 pb-10 last:pb-0">
      {i < phases.length - 1 && (
        <div class:list={["absolute left-[15px] top-7 w-0.5 h-full", p.status === 'current' ? "bg-emerald-500/40" : "bg-zinc-800"]} />
      )}
      <div class:list={[
        "absolute left-0 top-1.5 w-8 h-8 rounded-full border-2 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold",
        p.status === 'current' ? "border-emerald-500 bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-400" : "border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-900 text-zinc-500"
      ]}>
        {p.status === 'current' ? '▶' : i + 1}
      </div>
      <div class="pt-0.5">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <span class:list={[
            "text-xs font-mono px-2 py-0.5 rounded border",
            p.status === 'current' ? "bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-400 border-emerald-500/30" : "bg-zinc-800 text-zinc-500 border-zinc-700"
          ]}>{p.ver}</span>
          <span class:list={["font-semibold", p.status === 'current' ? "text-zinc-100" : "text-zinc-400"]}>{p.name}</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-zinc-600">{p.period}</span>
          {p.status === 'current' && <span class="text-xs bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-400 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full border border-emerald-500/30">In progress</span>}
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-1 mb-3">
          {p.items.map(item => (
            <li class:list={["flex items-start gap-2 text-sm", p.status === 'current' ? "text-zinc-300" : "text-zinc-500"]}>
              <span class:list={["mt-1.5 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full shrink-0", p.status === 'current' ? "bg-emerald-500" : "bg-zinc-700"]} />
              {item}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
        {p.not && (
          <div class="text-xs text-zinc-600">
            <span class="font-medium">Not in this release:</span> {p.not.join(', ')}
          </div>
        )}
      </div>
    </div>
  ))}
</div>

## Design Principles for the Roadmap

The spec as originally conceived was too ambitious for a solo founder. The revised sequencing follows a single rule: **ship less, ship sooner, ship well.**

- v0.1 proves offline works, nothing else
- Each release adds one new modality (audio → ecological evidence → camera traps → AI → AR)
- PITs and trails wait until the core observation loop is stable
- Institutional exports ship when there is data worth exporting

</DocLayout>
